{
  "text": "In this context, and considering prior evidence linking GBCr to glutamate transmission and neuroenergetics, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] we interpret the acute increases in PFC GBCr during ketamine infusion and its positive relationship to treatment response, as a supportive human evidence (1) that the ketamine-induced acute glutamate surge is putatively present in humans, [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] (2) that it contributes to the RAAD of the drug, [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] and (3) that PFC GBCr is a clinically relevant rigorous and reproducible biomarker of the underlying glutamate surge.",
  "correct_citation": {
